        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 1:15PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 114 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
northwest of Hiwasse, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Bella Vista...                    Gravette...
Hiwasse...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
